title: For Sale:  VIGILANCE RIFLES VR1 simiauto 408 CHEYTAC 23"       Reloading dies brass 420gr bullet bipod .408 case
postcontent:
Price just lowered!

Vigilance Rifles has filed bankruptcy so if you ever wanted a semi auto 408 cheytac this could be your last chance. On their last price 

list the rifle was $9,875 by itself before accessories like the extra magazine, $375 or hard case. Together this package would be well 

over $11,000.

Only the Buy it Now price gets you everything you see. Starting bid is for rifle, extra magazine ($375) and case only!

WE DO SHIP TO CALIFORNIA! It is up to you, the buyer, to make sure this is legal in your area, and if it is we are an approved seller to 

the state of California and are more than happy to serve you.

We are an FFL and will accept trade-ins, shipped to us or brought in locally, from individuals. No need to pay your FFL a fee for doing it 

when we can walk you through the process.

Hello and thank you for checking out our auction. Up for auction is a very lightly used Vigilance Rifles 408 Cheytac simiauto. You wont 

see many of these in your life, so take the opportunity to own one now. All of these rifles are truly custom. Just think about the size of a 

408 Cheytac shell in a simiauto rifle. This is truly Big Game hunting redefined. Any hunt, any country, any animal, is yours for the taking 

with this beast. The fluted barrel is 23 inches and 26 inches with the break. Very comfortable to shoot and optic ready. We have many 

hunting optics available just email us and ask.

Check them out in action: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NQO6a3Yg4TQ

Payment Methods: Visa, Mastercard, Western Union Money Transfer!!!

I also take trades like hunting rifles, tactical rifles, handguns and quality optics. Just email me directly at Justin@darcopsarmory.com 

or use the gunbroker ask seller a question feature and tell me what you have. Maybe we can work out a trade or use it as a partial down 

payment.

From Vigilance Rifles:
408 Cheytac. The Holy Grail of rifle cartridges, especially when being shot by the VR1 rifles. Quick follow up shots and easy impact 

reading from the low recoil of the VR1 Rifles is one of the key advantages of stepping down to a 408 Cheytac cartridge from the much 

bigger 416 Barrett or 50 BMG rifles. Not to mention VR1 rifles only weigh 18 lb. which means you can actually take it some where. It is 

the cartridge that I designed the VR1 rifles to shoot, all other calibers that we offer just happen to fit in the VR1 Rifles.

Rocky Mountain Bullets has developed real 420 gn. RBBT bullets for the 408 Cheytac, it certainly has taken the 408 Cheytac to a new 

level in performance. With the new bullets shooters are able to achieve long periods of sustained fire before accuracy deteriorates due 

to fouling, compared to shooting solid monolithics.

Distinctive from all others the VR1 is the only Semi-Auto Autoloader on the market chambered in the 408 Cheytac or 505 Gibbs. It is also 

available in 338 Lapua. The 408 Cheytac cartridge is a highbred, with confirmed kills out to 1 mile from trained hands. The VR1 holds 

five cartridges in 408 Cheytac - 505 Gibbs and 338 Lapua. The 338 Lapua is NATO and ammo is in military armaments, RAUFUS-AP-API 

are available, the cartridge proves well out to 1500 yards. VR1 shoots 1 MOA accuracy with 338 Lapua or 408 Cheytac in trained hands. 

The VR1 is not your typical M16 type conversion sniper rifle. We take great pride in the fact we completely manufacture it from the 

ground up. Our true 2-stage trigger with oil-lite bearings for a consistent reliable trigger pull. There are four sizes of bi pods and a 

mono pod available for different shooting requirements they change out in seconds. Our sling is attached to the internal frame of the 

rifle so an accidental dropping of the rifle due to sling pull is eliminated. The sling design also enables it to double as a turnacate. The 

Mill-Spec scope rail is mounted with (TORX-FHCS) this precision aligns the scope with the barrel eliminating bullet shift at different 

distances. Our safety is ambidextrous push type ( Fail Proof) with easy visual identification. We use a rotary screw bolt system that 

screws the bolt shut; this feature virtually eliminates the required force for opening and shutting the bolt. This is one of the key 

reasons that we are the only manufacturer able to make the 408 Cheytac cartridges shoot flawlessly in a Semi-Auto Autoloader. Rotary 

lock rifles usually use a spring loaded ejector, which can cause jams with high rate fire, the VR1 uses a Rotary screw bolt and fixed 

ejector for sure ejection and no jams. It is unusual to find a large caliber Semi-Auto Autoloader rifle that shoots as accurately and 

reliably as the VR1.

BENEFITS - A Long-range PRECISION SNIPER RIFLE (PSR) with quick follow up shots due to low recoil of Semi-Auto operation and Auto 

loading. Quick detachable magazines for instant load selection and increased firepower. Robust sturdy design that easily assembles 

and breaks down with no tools in under a minute with no loss of bullet impact. Easily concealable, no assembly being longer than 33 

inches. Variable caliber interchangeable barrels. A gas forward design allowing for longer periods before cleaning due to gases not 

entering the receiver area. Our list is long and all the innovations in this new rifle certainly cannot be described on a concise white 

paper. The technology and engineering in this rifle are instantly noticeable.

Features:
Designed and developed to be light and mobile and inspired by several of the finest autoloading rifles in the world, we have taken the 

best features and incorporated them into a larger than life autoloading rifle.

Chambered in four exciting large calibers, the 338 Lapua, 375 Cheytac, 408 Cheytac and 505 Gibbs. The 338 Lapua for NATO, 375 and 

408 Cheytac for long range engagement and the legendary 505 Gibbs made famous by Earnest Hemingway for unbeatable knockdown 

Power.

With five shots in the quick detachable magazine you’re sure to have plenty of firepower for the largest or most dangerous game.

Reliability of the VR1 is due to the gas port being optimally located to the chamber. The gases are cleaner and hotter up front and result 

in more reliable cycling and less fowling, the best autoloading rifles in the world use this system.

Our upper receiver is made from 17-4 PH Stainless Steel and certified Heat Treatment for high-pressure operation with such large 

calibers. The upper receiver-barrel locks securely into a lightweight hard-anodized lower receiver. The rifle uses a three-lugged rotary 

screw bolt for sure lockup, and a fixed ejector for high rate fire.

Using a 11/4 Bull Barrel for extreme accuracy and incorporating a proven Titanium Muzzle Brake for taming the Beast, makes the VR1 

easy to shoot in any of our four calibers. The VR1 Rifles come standard with our exclusive M1A style Glass Filled Nylon Stocks for all 

weather conditions and come standard with Coyote M1A CHEEKPAD. Optionally High Comb Stocks machined from (RUTPLY) premium 

wood are available in several colors.

Our exclusive Pendulum Two Stage Trigger (PTST) at the heart of the gun supplies crisp reliable trigger pull. First stage is 2-½ lb and 

second stage releases at 3-½ lb respectively, the predictability of the trigger improves shooter accuracy and confidence. Incorporated 

within the trigger system is a heavy engagement (FAIL PROOF) traditional push safety.


Shipping/handling for this rifle will be $75 due to size and weight. Insurance will be added, unless you request it not to be, and will cost 

1.75% of the price of the gun to cover potential damage or loss of the item in shipping. The price in this auction reflects a 5% discount 

for certified funds that is not given if you pay with a credit card. The value of all merchandise traded will be treated like certified funds; 

therefore, this item will still be subject to shipping and insurance charges. Because of additional paperwork and time to process the 

shipment, California orders on firearms will be charged an additional $25 transfer fee. If wiring funds there will be a $25 charge.

reading from the low recoil of the VR1 Rifles is one of the key advantages of stepping down to a 408 Cheytac cartridge from the much 

bigger 416 Barrett or 50 BMG rifles. Not to mention VR1 rifles only weigh 18 lb. which means you can actually take it some where. It is 

the cartridge that I designed the VR1 rifles to shoot, all other calibers that we offer just happen to fit in the VR1 Rifles.

level in performance. With the new bullets shooters are able to achieve long periods of sustained fire before accuracy deteriorates due 

to fouling, compared to shooting solid monolithics.

available in 338 Lapua. The 408 Cheytac cartridge is a highbred, with confirmed kills out to 1 mile from trained hands. The VR1 holds 

five cartridges in 408 Cheytac - 505 Gibbs and 338 Lapua. The 338 Lapua is NATO and ammo is in military armaments, RAUFUS-AP-API 

are available, the cartridge proves well out to 1500 yards. VR1 shoots 1 MOA accuracy with 338 Lapua or 408 Cheytac in trained hands.

ground up. Our true 2-stage trigger with oil-lite bearings for a consistent reliable trigger pull. There are four sizes of bi pods and a 

mono pod available for different shooting requirements they change out in seconds. Our sling is attached to the internal frame of the 

rifle so an accidental dropping of the rifle due to sling pull is eliminated. The sling design also enables it to double as a turnacate. The 

Mill-Spec scope rail is mounted with (TORX-FHCS) this precision aligns the scope with the barrel eliminating bullet shift at different 

distances. Our safety is ambidextrous push type ( Fail Proof) with easy visual identification. We use a rotary screw bolt system that 

screws the bolt shut; this feature virtually eliminates the required force for opening and shutting the bolt. This is one of the key 

reasons that we are the only manufacturer able to make the 408 Cheytac cartridges shoot flawlessly in a Semi-Auto Autoloader. Rotary 

lock rifles usually use a spring loaded ejector, which can cause jams with high rate fire, the VR1 uses a Rotary screw bolt and fixed 

ejector for sure ejection and no jams. It is unusual to find a large caliber Semi-Auto Autoloader rifle that shoots as accurately and 

reliably as the VR1.

BENEFITS - A Long-range PRECISION SNIPER RIFLE (PSR) with quick follow up shots due to low recoil of Semi-Auto operation and Auto 

loading. Quick detachable magazines for instant load selection and increased firepower. Robust sturdy design that easily assembles

Reliability of the VR1 is due to the gas port being optimally located to the chamber. The gases are cleaner and hotter up front and result 

in more reliable cycling and less fowling, the best autoloading rifles in the world use this system.

Our upper receiver is made from 17-4 PH Stainless Steel and certified Heat Treatment for high-pressure operation with such large 

calibers. The upper receiver-barrel locks securely into a lightweight hard-anodized lower receiver. The rifle uses a three-lugged rotary 

screw bolt for sure lockup, and a fixed ejector for high rate fire.

Using a 11/4 Bull Barrel for extreme accuracy and incorporating a proven Titanium Muzzle Brake for taming the Beast, makes the VR1 

easy to shoot in any of our four calibers. The VR1 Rifles come standard with our exclusive M1A style Glass Filled Nylon Stocks for all 

weather conditions and come standard with Coyote M1A CHEEKPAD. Optionally High Comb Stocks machined from (RUTPLY) premium 

wood are available in several colors.

second stage releases at 3-½ lb respectively, the predictability of the trigger improves shooter accuracy and confidence. Incorporated 

within the trigger system is a heavy engagement (FAIL PROOF) traditional push safety.

title: For Sale:  VIGILANCE RIFLES VR1 simiauto 408 CHEYTAC 23"       Reloading dies brass 420gr bullet bipod .408 case
postcontent:
Price just lowered!

Vigilance Rifles has filed bankruptcy so if you ever wanted a semi auto 408 cheytac this could be your last chance. On their last price 

list the rifle was $9,875 by itself before accessories like the extra magazine, $375 or hard case. Together this package would be well 

over $11,000.

Only the Buy it Now price gets you everything you see. Starting bid is for rifle, extra magazine ($375) and case only!

WE DO SHIP TO CALIFORNIA! It is up to you, the buyer, to make sure this is legal in your area, and if it is we are an approved seller to 

the state of California and are more than happy to serve you.

We are an FFL and will accept trade-ins, shipped to us or brought in locally, from individuals. No need to pay your FFL a fee for doing it 

when we can walk you through the process.

Hello and thank you for checking out our auction. Up for auction is a very lightly used Vigilance Rifles 408 Cheytac simiauto. You wont 

see many of these in your life, so take the opportunity to own one now. All of these rifles are truly custom. Just think about the size of a 

408 Cheytac shell in a simiauto rifle. This is truly Big Game hunting redefined. Any hunt, any country, any animal, is yours for the taking 

with this beast. The fluted barrel is 23 inches and 26 inches with the break. Very comfortable to shoot and optic ready. We have many 

hunting optics available just email us and ask.

Check them out in action: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NQO6a3Yg4TQ

Payment Methods: Visa, Mastercard, Western Union Money Transfer!!!

I also take trades like hunting rifles, tactical rifles, handguns and quality optics. Just email me directly at Justin@darcopsarmory.com 

or use the gunbroker ask seller a question feature and tell me what you have. Maybe we can work out a trade or use it as a partial down 

payment.

From Vigilance Rifles:
408 Cheytac. The Holy Grail of rifle cartridges, especially when being shot by the VR1 rifles. Quick follow up shots and easy impact 

reading from the low recoil of the VR1 Rifles is one of the key advantages of stepping down to a 408 Cheytac cartridge from the much 

bigger 416 Barrett or 50 BMG rifles. Not to mention VR1 rifles only weigh 18 lb. which means you can actually take it some where. It is 

the cartridge that I designed the VR1 rifles to shoot, all other calibers that we offer just happen to fit in the VR1 Rifles.

Rocky Mountain Bullets has developed real 420 gn. RBBT bullets for the 408 Cheytac, it certainly has taken the 408 Cheytac to a new 

level in performance. With the new bullets shooters are able to achieve long periods of sustained fire before accuracy deteriorates due 

to fouling, compared to shooting solid monolithics.

Distinctive from all others the VR1 is the only Semi-Auto Autoloader on the market chambered in the 408 Cheytac or 505 Gibbs. It is also 

available in 338 Lapua. The 408 Cheytac cartridge is a highbred, with confirmed kills out to 1 mile from trained hands. The VR1 holds 

five cartridges in 408 Cheytac - 505 Gibbs and 338 Lapua. The 338 Lapua is NATO and ammo is in military armaments, RAUFUS-AP-API 

are available, the cartridge proves well out to 1500 yards. VR1 shoots 1 MOA accuracy with 338 Lapua or 408 Cheytac in trained hands. 

The VR1 is not your typical M16 type conversion sniper rifle. We take great pride in the fact we completely manufacture it from the 

ground up. Our true 2-stage trigger with oil-lite bearings for a consistent reliable trigger pull. There are four sizes of bi pods and a 

mono pod available for different shooting requirements they change out in seconds. Our sling is attached to the internal frame of the 

rifle so an accidental dropping of the rifle due to sling pull is eliminated. The sling design also enables it to double as a turnacate. The 

Mill-Spec scope rail is mounted with (TORX-FHCS) this precision aligns the scope with the barrel eliminating bullet shift at different 

distances. Our safety is ambidextrous push type ( Fail Proof) with easy visual identification. We use a rotary screw bolt system that 

screws the bolt shut; this feature virtually eliminates the required force for opening and shutting the bolt. This is one of the key 

reasons that we are the only manufacturer able to make the 408 Cheytac cartridges shoot flawlessly in a Semi-Auto Autoloader. Rotary 

lock rifles usually use a spring loaded ejector, which can cause jams with high rate fire, the VR1 uses a Rotary screw bolt and fixed 

ejector for sure ejection and no jams. It is unusual to find a large caliber Semi-Auto Autoloader rifle that shoots as accurately and 

reliably as the VR1.

BENEFITS - A Long-range PRECISION SNIPER RIFLE (PSR) with quick follow up shots due to low recoil of Semi-Auto operation and Auto 

loading. Quick detachable magazines for instant load selection and increased firepower. Robust sturdy design that easily assembles 

and breaks down with no tools in under a minute with no loss of bullet impact. Easily concealable, no assembly being longer than 33 

inches. Variable caliber interchangeable barrels. A gas forward design allowing for longer periods before cleaning due to gases not 

entering the receiver area. Our list is long and all the innovations in this new rifle certainly cannot be described on a concise white 

paper. The technology and engineering in this rifle are instantly noticeable.

Features:
Designed and developed to be light and mobile and inspired by several of the finest autoloading rifles in the world, we have taken the 

best features and incorporated them into a larger than life autoloading rifle.

Chambered in four exciting large calibers, the 338 Lapua, 375 Cheytac, 408 Cheytac and 505 Gibbs. The 338 Lapua for NATO, 375 and 

408 Cheytac for long range engagement and the legendary 505 Gibbs made famous by Earnest Hemingway for unbeatable knockdown 

Power.

With five shots in the quick detachable magazine you’re sure to have plenty of firepower for the largest or most dangerous game.

Reliability of the VR1 is due to the gas port being optimally located to the chamber. The gases are cleaner and hotter up front and result 

in more reliable cycling and less fowling, the best autoloading rifles in the world use this system.

Our upper receiver is made from 17-4 PH Stainless Steel and certified Heat Treatment for high-pressure operation with such large 

calibers. The upper receiver-barrel locks securely into a lightweight hard-anodized lower receiver. The rifle uses a three-lugged rotary 

screw bolt for sure lockup, and a fixed ejector for high rate fire.

Using a 11/4 Bull Barrel for extreme accuracy and incorporating a proven Titanium Muzzle Brake for taming the Beast, makes the VR1 

easy to shoot in any of our four calibers. The VR1 Rifles come standard with our exclusive M1A style Glass Filled Nylon Stocks for all 

weather conditions and come standard with Coyote M1A CHEEKPAD. Optionally High Comb Stocks machined from (RUTPLY) premium 

wood are available in several colors.

Our exclusive Pendulum Two Stage Trigger (PTST) at the heart of the gun supplies crisp reliable trigger pull. First stage is 2-½ lb and 

second stage releases at 3-½ lb respectively, the predictability of the trigger improves shooter accuracy and confidence. Incorporated 

within the trigger system is a heavy engagement (FAIL PROOF) traditional push safety.


Shipping/handling for this rifle will be $75 due to size and weight. Insurance will be added, unless you request it not to be, and will cost 

1.75% of the price of the gun to cover potential damage or loss of the item in shipping. The price in this auction reflects a 5% discount 

for certified funds that is not given if you pay with a credit card. The value of all merchandise traded will be treated like certified funds; 

therefore, this item will still be subject to shipping and insurance charges. Because of additional paperwork and time to process the 

shipment, California orders on firearms will be charged an additional $25 transfer fee. If wiring funds there will be a $25 charge.

For sale is a sporterized Swedish Mauser M94/14 in the classic 6.5 x 55 caliber. Interarms, long ago, imported a number of these hard to find classics. To identify these carbines as "theirs", they scrubbed the year of manufacture commonly found on the breech and roll marked "Interarms G33/50".

The barrel is 18 inches long making this ideal for those of you who brush hunt deer, etc. Add maneuverability to the legendary accuracy of the 6.5 x 55 cartridge and what's not to like.

title: For Sale:  COLT LE CARBINE LE6940 AR15 5.56MM
postcontent:
The Colt LE6940 Advanced Law Enforcement Carbine is best thought of as a semi-automatic-only version of the M4 modified with Colt’s proprietary monolithic one-piece upper receiver and handguard. 

This upper receiver traces its origins back some six years to guns Colt produced for the SCAR (Special Operations Forces Combat Assault Rifle) program of the U.S. Special Operations Command (SOCOM). It is designed to obviate the need for a separate multiple-rail handguard for mounting accessories, affording perfect alignment of accessories mounted in-line with the primary optical device, providing extreme rigidity, and allowing the removal and reinstallation of optics without loss of zero. Additionally, the handguard section provides sufficient ventilation to prevent heat buildup around the barrel. And the monolithic upper weighs less than a standard upper receiver with separate quad-rail handguard attached. 

The upper, made from a CNC-machined 7075-T6 aluminum forging, features integral top and side Picatinny rails extending forward just to the rear of the gas block. Recesses for quick-detachable sling swivels are located on both side rails. The bottom rail is a separate piece that can be detached for cleaning or installation of under-barrel accessories. All rail sections have numbered slots for repeatable installation of devices. The LE6940 has extensive parts commonality with the M4, sharing the barrel’s chrome-lining, four-position collapsible stock, and birdcage-style flash hider. Also present are the familiar shell deflector, ejection port cover and forward assist. The LE6940’s bolt, carrier and trigger mechanism also follow the proven AR-15 pattern, as do the controls on the lower receiver: magazine release, reversible safety and bolt release. Like all current Colt-produced rifles, the LE6940 uses 0.154-inch-diameter hammer and trigger pins. 

The 1:7-inch twist of the barrel and 5.56x45 mm NATO chamber allow the use of 55-grain, 62-grain and 77-grain ammunition. The M4-style barrel measures 0.750 inches at the gas block, but decreases to 0.640 inches under the handguard, and incorporates the M4-style step. Barrel attachment is by way of an improved barrel nut that reportedly offers greater strength. Specifications Action Semi-Automatic Caliber 223 Remington/5.56 NATO Bbl Length 16.1" Capacity 30+1 Trigger Direct Safety Lever OAL 35.25" Weight 6.6 lbs Stock 4-Position Collapsible Finish Black.

title: For Sale/Trade:  50 rounds of 44 S&W - 44 American - 44 Bulldog
location: Sharon PA to Akron Ohio, Cleveland, Ohio
postcontent:
I have fifty rounds of .44 S&W which is a round with a case shorter than .44 Special.  the case is less than an inch, whereas the .44 Special or .44 S&W Special has a case longer than an inch.  It was used in some older guns and seems to be the same as the S&W Russian.  I had an old .44 Bulldog revolver which used this ammo but have sold it.  Check to see whether it is appropriate for your weapon.  These cases are headstamped as .44 S&W Special but, because they are shorter than .44 special, they may have been cut down from longer cases to make this shorter version.  Be sure to check to see if an old weapon is safe and can fire these loads.  Some really old .44 S&W or .44 American revolvers used black powder cartridges and would not be safe with these smokeless loads. 

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.44_S%26W_American

I purchased this a while back. I installed it but never used it. I have since went with something else and no longer need this one. It's listed for the Mossberg 930 but I don't see why it wouldn't fit in any 12 gauge magazine tube since all 12 gauge is the same size. 

From GG&G's website:

Mossberg 930 Shotgun Shooters want the best for their shotguns. The standard Mossberg 930 follower does not offer the upgraded features tactical shooters are looking for. It is one of the first 930 shotgun components to be upgraded. The GG&G Mossberg 930 Follower for Mossberg 12 ga. shotguns is an enhanced follower manufactured with the Mossberg Shotgun Shooter in mind.
 - Installs just like the factory 930 follower. No modification to the shotgun required.
 - The GG&G Mossberg Follower is manufactured from stainless steel for corrosion and wear resistance. The stainless steel body provides smooth operation and resists galling and contaminants imbedding into the body of the follower. These are the two major contributors to aftermarket followers malfunctioning.
 - The high visibility red insert is aluminum and is manufactured so that you cannot only quickly see that the magazine tube is empty, but in low light conditions, feel the difference between the face of the follower and the rear of a shotgun shell.
 - The follower is manufactured with a deep spring pocket to better control spring movement.

I will ship in a regular envelope for an extra $1
